<br>
Look, I don't *want* to start a price war. I agree that it would suck for all tradeskillers involved. We've already nuked the Demi-Sec market (and Azhrei,  your cost-to-create estimate's a little low, closer to 30 [opal and gold bar]). The odd bottle will trickle out at 200, assuming the buyer's motivated enough. I find most of the people who are habitual PotC'ers are looking more at 150. My gripe was that I was trying *not* to screw things up for everyone, and some d00d (a halfling dr00d, amusingly enough) insisted on undercutting whomever had the lowest price. I retaliated last night, and they appeared to not be online when I got on this morning. We'll see how things look when I get home after dinner. In the meantime, I reset my retail price to match the other person selling in the Bazaar at the time, because they deserve to sell their Demi-Sec just as much as I do, and while I <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>could</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> sell for less to take a bigger marketshare, I would rather just share the market.<br>
<br>
At any rate some responses:<br>
<br>
Dorphen: You don't like the markup? <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> You</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> go spend 9 hours doing a nine-item combine with a non-stackable container, and then you can make your own. My wrists will never be the same again.<br>
<br>
Azhrei: One thing you didn't include was (as Jarkell pointed out) the <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>value</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> of the item. If I tried to sell a +5 WIS, +5 INT, +5 DEX, +5 AGI belt for 10PP, I would be hunted down and summarily shot by the tradeskill community. Some of these stat beverages are pretty nice. I think the mark-ups, while higher in percentage than JC, are reasonable, given the relatively low cost of the components. I should think that having +6 STR and +6 STA would be worth 10PP to a struggling tank (or even a successful one).<br>
<br>
Kiron: I do have fun -- crafting. Where my enjoyment typically stops is when I walk into the Bazaar and set up for Trader and start eyeballing the other prices to make sure I'm not out-of-line with the market.<br>
<br>
Jarkell: heh, I'm <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> still</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> trying to recover the cost of my corking device. Too bad Demi-Sec doesn't require it, it would eliminate a lot of the competition...People are already asking me when I'm going to go for a Grandmaster Trophy, and I just snickered; I've never seen that much money at once (gem costs).<br>
<br>
Anyhoosy, peace, love, and other indoor sports.<br>
<br>
Cheers,<br>
