<br>
The problem here is that this is an item on the mainline skilling route which does not stack. You either vendor them (a horrible idea) or sell them off cheap to clear space. This should be especially true on FV as we do not have alts to pass them off to. <br>
<br>
On that server I have seen tradeskilled items at less than manufactured cost - eg. Silver ruby veil 100pp. Now that is not an item anyone makes for skilling so unless it was a dropped ruby used casually then I consider such pricing stupid.<br>
<br>
The other issue is how much time you want to spend in the bazaar. I tradeskill partly for enjoyment, and partly for quest-related skills. If I ever make a profit I will be happily surprised. My motivation then, is to get whatever I have made shifted fast and get back out on the hunt or whatever. If I had a second account and a permanent connection then leaving a trader on 24/7 waiting for the &quot;market&quot; price might make sense. If I just filled my bank with something I need to move it fast so I can keep on skilling. <br>
<br>
Motivation varies and profit is not always the reason people do things. One story I treasure on that theme is the woman who sold a Jaguar (car) for £10 - it was her ex-husbands car and she had been directed to &quot;sell it and send him the proceeds&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
